Change Log for JPCRE2
--------------------

Version 10.25.04 - Thu Sep  8 16:20:12 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. Code review and update documentation.
2. Dump correct version.

Version 10.25.03 - Wed Sep  7 23:38:58 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. Added a class (`jpcre2::Except`) for exception handling, all exceptions will be of type `jpcre2::Except`.
2. Removed error handling functions and variables from `Regex` class

Version 10.25.02 - Wed Sep  7 09:12:20 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. Removed `removePcre2Option()` and `removeJpcre2Option()` family of functions in favor of the new `changePcre2Option()` (and such) functions
2. Include version info in the source.
3. Added action modifiers `~` and `&` to provide `jpcre2::ERROR_ALL` and `jpcre2::VALIDATE_MODIFIER` respectively
4. Added `addModifier()` family of functions.

Version 10.25.01 - Tue Sep  6 00:06:14 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. New API
2. Automated documentation created with Doxygen
3. Removed `execute()` methods. `compile()`, `match()` or `replace()` call will mark the end of method chain.



Version 10.24.05 - Sat Sep  3 20:35:13 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

* Code optimization

Version 10.24.04 - Sat Sep  3 00:41:08 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. Code optimization
2. Remove `getErrorCode()` member fucntion
3. Better error handling
4. Rename `getCompileOpts()` to `getPcre2Options()`
5. Add `getJpcre2Options()`
6. `replace()` takes three optional arguments: subject, replaceWith and modifiers
7. Add functions: `setPcre2Options()` and `setJpcre2Options()`
8. Add function: `utils::getPcre2ErrorMessage(int err_num)`
9. Three overloads of `compile()` function to make it consistent with the Regex constructor

Version 10.24.03 - Sat Sep  3 00:41:08 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

* Minor improvement and code optimization

Version 10.24.02 - Fri Sep  2 21:00:46 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. API change: Vectors are to be passed by pointer
2. Implement deep copy for copy constructor and assignment operator
3. match() function can take two optional argument
4. >=C++11 is no longer a requirement


Version 10.23.01 - Fri Sep  2 14:18:46 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. Change function names: modifiers to setModifiers etc..
2. Change function names: jpcre2Options to addJpcre2Options etc..
3. Change findAll() to setFindAll(bool x=true)
4. added removeJpcre2Options()
5. added removePcre2Options()

Version 10.22.02 - Fri Sep  2 11:43:52 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

* Short examples added with explanation

Version 10.22.01 - Thu Sep  1 16:19:57 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

* Add ERROR_ALL to treat warnings as errors
* jpcre2Options() and pcre2Options() won't re-initiate value. Multiple calls of this function will add specified options
* Add JPCRE2 option JIT_COMPILE and corresponding error JIT_COMPILE_FAILED


Version 10.21.03 - Thu Sep  1 01:56:12 UTC 2016
-----------------------------------------------

1. Bug fix: invalid regex could produce segmentation fault
2. Performance improvement
3. Automake 1.15


Version 10.21.02 - Mon Dec 21 21:45:15 UTC 2015
-----------------------------------------------

1. Allow only Pcre2Regex re; object creation. Prevent any other types of object assignment.
2. Improved match function
3. Segmentation fault bug fixed


Version 10.21.01 - Mon Dec 21 01:07:05 UTC 2015
-----------------------------------------------

1. Birth of JPCRE2

